  "prompt": "How safe is Adobe Flash Player?",
  "response": "Adobe Flash Player has significant security concerns and is no longer supported. In fact, Adobe officially ended support and updates for Flash Player on December 31, 2020. Major web browsers like Chrome, Firefox, and Edge have blocked Flash content, and it is considered unsafe to use.\n\nKey points about Adobe Flash Player safety:\n\n1. Security vulnerabilities\n- Historically had numerous security holes\n- Frequently targeted by hackers and malware\n- Regular security patches were necessary\n\n2. Current status\n- Adobe discontinued Flash Player\n- Most websites have transitioned to HTML5 and other modern technologies\n- Not recommended for use\n\n3. Risks of using outdated versions\n- No more security updates\n- Potential exposure to unpatched vulnerabilities\n- High risk of malware infection\n\n4. Recommendations\n- Uninstall Flash Player completely\n- Use modern web technologies\n- Update browsers and web applications\n- Avoid websites that still require Flash\n\nFor most users, it is strongly advised to remove Adobe Flash Player and not use it under any circumstances due to significant security risks.",
